trend_summary: Across the series the street grid, golf course and airport remain constant, confirming slow-changing suburban fabric. Growth is limited to scattered infill homes and a refurbished central commercial block, while tree cover thickens along residential lots. On the coast, tidal marsh expands and gains vegetation, signalling shoreline restoration rather than reclamation.
notable_changes: Incremental infill housing on vacant residential lots, especially south-central neighbourhoods.
Modernisation/roof replacement of the large rectangular commercial warehouse near the centre.
Tree canopy expansion along streets and on private parcels, indicating maturing vegetation.
